Ralph B. Thomas, CFA
Senior Vice President
Portfolio Management
Investment Committee Member
Ralph B. Thomas is a Senior Vice President at Fayez Sarofim & Co. and a member of the Firm’s Investment Committee.  He is also a portfolio manager for a variety of institutional and high net worth clients.  Mr. Thomas joined the Firm in 1968 as an Associate, after completing an internship in the summer of 1967.  Over the years, areas of research responsibility have included utilities, railroads, autos, oil service, chemicals and capital goods.
Mr. Thomas received both a M.B.A. in 1969 and a B.B.A. in Finance in 1966 from the University of Texas.
Mr. Thomas is a member of the University of Texas System Chancellor’s Council, a lifetime member of the UT McCombs School of Business Advisory Council, a member of the UT McDonald Observatory Advisory Council and a member and past Chairman of both the University of Texas College of Business Administration Foundation Advisory Council and the Development Board for the University of Texas Health Science Center of Houston.  He is also a Director of the Lonestar Flight Museum and was the Vice Chairman of the Texas World Trade Council, appointed by the Governor of Texas.  

